  "chapter": {
    "number": 14,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Restoration for Israel"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "For the LORD will have compassion on Jacob; once again He will choose Israel and settle them in their own land. The foreigner will join them and unite with the house of Jacob."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "The nations will escort Israel and bring it to its homeland.",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          "Then the house of Israel will possess the nations as menservants and maidservants in the LORD’s land. They will make captives of their captors and rule over their oppressors."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Fall of the King of Babylon"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "On the day that the LORD gives you rest from your pain and torment, and from the hard labor into which you were forced,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "you will sing this song of contempt against the king of Babylon:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "How the oppressor has ceased,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and how his fury",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2566
          },
          {
            "text": "has ended!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD has broken the staff of the wicked,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the scepter of the rulers.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "It struck the peoples in anger",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with unceasing blows;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "it subdued the nations in rage",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with relentless persecution.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "All the earth is at peace and at rest;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they break out in song.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Even the cypresses",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2567
          },
          {
            "text": "and cedars of Lebanon",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "exult over you:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "“Since you have been laid low,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "no woodcutter comes against us.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Sheol beneath is eager",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to meet you upon your arrival.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "It stirs the spirits of the dead to greet you—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "all the rulers of the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "It makes all the kings of the nations",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "rise from their thrones.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They will all respond to you, saying,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“You too have become weak, as we are;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "you have become like us!”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your pomp has been brought down to Sheol,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "along with the music of your harps.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Maggots are your bed",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and worms your blanket.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "How you have fallen from heaven,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O day star,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2568
          },
          {
            "text": "son of the dawn!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You have been cut down to the ground,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O destroyer of nations.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You said in your heart:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“I will ascend to the heavens;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will raise my throne",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "above the stars of God.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will sit on the mount of assembly,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in the far reaches of the north.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2569
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will ascend above the tops of the clouds;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will make myself like the Most High.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But you will be brought down to Sheol,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to the lowest depths of the Pit.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Those who see you will stare;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will ponder your fate:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "“Is this the man who shook the earth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and made the kingdoms tremble,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "who turned the world into a desert",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and destroyed its cities,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who refused to let the captives",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "return to their homes?”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "All the kings of the nations lie in state,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "each in his own tomb.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2570
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But you are cast out of your grave like a rejected branch,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "covered by those slain with the sword,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and dumped into a rocky pit",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a carcass trampled underfoot.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You will not join them in burial,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "since you have destroyed your land",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and slaughtered your own people.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The offspring of the wicked",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will never again be mentioned.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prepare a place to slaughter his sons",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for the iniquities of their forefathers.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They will never rise up to possess a land",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or cover the earth with their cities.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“I will rise up against them,”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "declares the LORD of Hosts.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "“I will cut off from Babylon",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "her name and her remnant,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "her offspring and her posterity,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the LORD."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“I will make her a place",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for owls and for swamplands;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will sweep her away",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with the broom of destruction,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "declares the LORD of Hosts.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "God’s Purpose against Assyria"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          "The LORD of Hosts has sworn:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Surely, as I have planned, so will it be;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as I have purposed, so will it stand.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will break Assyria in My land;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will trample him on My mountain.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "His yoke will be taken off My people,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and his burden removed from their shoulders.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "This is the plan devised for the whole earth,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and this is the hand stretched out over all the nations.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD of Hosts has purposed,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and who can thwart Him?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "His hand is outstretched,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so who can turn it back?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Philistia Will Be Destroyed"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          "In the year that King Ahaz died, this burden was received:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not rejoice, all you Philistines,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that the rod that struck you is broken.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For a viper will spring from the root of the snake,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a flying serpent from its egg.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 30,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then the firstborn of the poor will find pasture,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the needy will lie down in safety,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "but I will kill your root by famine,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your remnant will be slain.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 31,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Wail, O gate! Cry out, O city!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Melt away, all you Philistines!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For a cloud of smoke comes from the north,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and there are no stragglers in its ranks.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 32,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What answer will be given",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to the envoys of that nation?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "“The LORD has founded Zion,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "where His afflicted people will find refuge.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
